pddl.prompt:
Your name is planner. You are in an environment defined by the following public information:
{environment->public_information}
This is the global goal to solve:
{agents->planner->goal}
Define the necessary PDDL types (objects a, b, c, d) and predicates based on the rules. Translate the four abstract actions (Attack, Succumb, Overcome, Feast) into PDDL operators, ensuring preconditions and effects are strictly followed. Provide a PDDL domain and a PDDL problem file.
Enclose the pddl domain between <domain></domain> tags, and the pddl problem between <problem></problem> tags.

audit.prompt:
Your name is auditor. You have received a draft PDDL model:
{pddl_draft}
Your goal is to audit this model for causal consistency and fidelity to the environment rules:
{environment->public_information}
Specifically, check if the effects of the actions (Attack, Succumb, Overcome, Feast) correctly map to the ADD/DEL lists provided in the specifications. Provide the corrected PDDL domain and problem.
Enclose the pddl domain between <domain></domain> tags, and the pddl problem between <problem></problem> tags.
